'''Modern expressionism''' is an alternative term for [[Symbolism (arts)|Symbolism]].<ref>Arnold Hauser, ''The Social History of Art'', Routledge, 1999, pxxxvii. {{ISBN|041519945X}}</ref> Visual artists described as modern expressionist include the American painter [[Marcus Jansen]] South African [[Gerard Sekoto]], whose work in the 1940s drew on [[Fauvism]] and [[Post-Impressionism]].<ref>Olu Oguibe in Rasheed Araeen, Sean Cubitt, Ziauddin Sardar, ''The Third Text Reader on Art, Culture and Theory'', Continuum International Publishing Group, 2002, p43. {{ISBN|0826458513}}</ref>

